cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.CR 

This paper deals with machine learning problems such as classification, clustering, and ranking, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper proposes a new generalization bound for the associated classifier based on the algorithmic robustness framework, which is a common theme in machine learning research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, and cs.CR.
